\cf0 We thus assume that a 1 ha ATS facility can be built for $1M. One person-day is required for harvesting; with a five-day workweek and weekly harvesting, one person can thus operate 5 ha of ATS. Harvesting and biomass handling are skilled tasks, thus an operator might command a salary of $50,000. We adopt the current floway lifetime assumption of 20 years, and a ratio of OpEx to CapEx of 10%. Our better-case scenario assumes lower CapEx and OpEx, and a 40-year floway lifetime, anticipating that with experience, improvements will be made to floway engineering, and that not all locations will require the same level of investment. For additional thoughts on ATS CapEx and OpEx, see \{Yun et al., 2015, #44995\}.}